  &lt;p id="JN5It8"&gt;&lt;em&gt;The New York Times &lt;/em&gt;Tech Guild went on strike at 12:01AM ET today, &lt;a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/style/media/2024/11/04/new-york-times-tech-strike-walkout/"&gt;reports &lt;em&gt;The Washington Post&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. The &lt;a href="https://nytimesguild.org/tech-contract-campaign/"&gt;guild represents&lt;/a&gt; over 600 software engineers, product managers, data analysts, and designers for the media company. Its strike leaves the company bereft of crucial technical expertise just one day before Election Day, when the &lt;em&gt;Times’&lt;/em&gt; crucial backend systems will be under very heavy stress.&lt;/p&gt;
